        {
            "id": 1,
            "question": "Explain the difference between a regular function return and a generator yield.",
            "preferredAnswer": "A function with return executes fully and returns a single value, terminating immediately.\n\nA function with yield pauses execution, returns a value, and remembers where it left off. When called again, it resumes right after the yield statement. This allows for lazy evaluation and memory efficiency, especially with large datasets."
        },
        {
            "id": 2,
            "question": "Write a decorator that prints 'Start' and 'End' around a function call.",
            "preferredAnswer": "def timer_decorator(func):\n    def wrapper(*args, **kwargs):\n        print('Start')\n        result = func(*args, **kwargs)\n        print('End')\n        return result\n    return wrapper\n\n@timer_decorator\ndef greet(name):\n    print(f'Hello {name}')\n\ngreet('Alice')"
        },
        {
