            "question": "Why should you put your venv folder in .gitignore?",
            "preferredAnswer": "Because virtual environments contain thousands of downloaded library files specific to your machine and operating system. If committed:\n1. It bloats repository size.\n2. It causes conflicts when others clone it on different OS (e.g., macOS vs Windows).\n3. Users might accidentally install those packages instead of installing fresh dependencies."
