        {
            "id": 5,
            "question": "What is the purpose of the `if __name__ == '__main__':` block?",
            "preferredAnswer": "It ensures the code inside only runs if the script is executed directly, not when imported as a module.\n\nExample:\nimport mymodule\n# If I imported mymodule elsewhere, I don't want the main block running instantly.\nif __name__ == '__main__':\n    main()\n\nThis promotes reusability of code."
        }
